content.problemStatement:
In C++, the `break` statement inside a switch block serves a crucial purpose. It terminates the current switch statement execution and transfers control to the statement following the switch block. Without break statements, C++ would execute all statements in all subsequent cases regardless of whether they match the expression (this is called "falling through").

**Syntax:**
```cpp
switch (expression) {
    case constant1:
        // Code block executed when expression equals constant1
        break; // Terminates the switch statement execution
    case constant2:
        // Code block executed when expression equals constant2
        break;
    case constant3:
        // Code block executed when expression equals constant3
        break;
    default:
        // Code block executed when no match is found
        break; // Optional but recommended for consistency
}
```
---

**Example:**
```cpp
#include 
using namespace std;

int main() {
    // Variable to represent a grade category (1=A, 2=B, 3=C, 4=D, 5=F)
    int gradeCategory = 2;

    cout << "Your performance is ";

    // Using switch to provide feedback based on grade category
    switch (gradeCategory) {
        case 1:
            cout << "excellent! You've earned an A.";
            break; // Stop here if gradeCategory is 1

        case 2:
            cout << "very good. You've earned a B.";
            break; // Stop here if gradeCategory is 2

        case 3:
            cout << "satisfactory. You've earned a C.";
            break; // Stop here if gradeCategory is 3

        case 4:
            cout << "passing, but needs improvement. You've earned a D.";
            break; // Stop here if gradeCategory is 4

        case 5:
            cout << "unsatisfactory. You've earned an F.";
            break; // Stop here if gradeCategory is 5

        default:
            cout << "unknown - invalid grade category.";
            break; // Stop here if gradeCategory doesn't match any case
    }

    return 0;
}
```

## Expected Output:
```default
Your performance is very good. You've earned a B.
```

